1
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,767
<i> Goodbye, Conde.</i>

2
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:26,167
<i> Mando is gone.</i>

3
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:27,433
<i> Sir, your wound.</i>

4
00:00:27,567 --> 00:00:29,900
<i>Didn't I tell you not
to interfere in Mando's case?</i>

5
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:32,133
<i>You don't understand what
I'm trying to tell you!</i>

6
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:34,300
<i>Yes, okay, you're good,
but what are you going to do?</i>

7
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:36,200
<i>What are you going to do when...</i>

8
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:38,333
<i> Sir, Sir, they're here, Sir.</i>

9
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:40,567
<i>Wait! It'll take some time
before they can come up here.</i>

10
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:42,233
<i>- Here! Here!
- Sir, Sir...</i>

11
00:00:42,367 --> 00:00:44,133
<i>- He's dead, Sir.
- De Jesus, call Chief.</i>

12
00:00:44,267 --> 00:00:45,967
<i> How's Mando?</i>

13
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:49,333
<i>Did he admit who shamelessly
let him escape from prison?</i>

14
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:51,267
<i>No information was obtained
from him.</i>

15
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,533
<i>The important thing is,
your sister is safe,</i>

16
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:54,867
<i> and in the hospital, now.</i>

17
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,400
<i>Bobby, Dad sent me here
to check up on you.</i>

18
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:58,500
<i> It's okay, I'm okay.</i>

19
00:00:58,633 --> 00:01:00,633
<i>- Bobby!
- Sir, why did you go out?</i>

20
00:01:00,767 --> 00:01:02,067
<i>You're really stubborn,
aren't you?</i>

21
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:04,300
<i>I'm sorry.
Something might happen to you.</i>

22
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:08,733
<i>I can't take that. So if it's
okay, can we start again?</i>

23
00:01:10,267 --> 00:01:11,367
Please.

24
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:23,300
But please, Sir, can you lessen
your stubbornness?

25
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:25,933
Otherwise,
I'll shoot you myself.

26
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:32,300
I'll shoot you in the legs
so you can't walk,

27
00:01:32,433 --> 00:01:33,933
and you can rest well.

28
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:07,733
Not for now, Mira,
but like I said,

29
00:02:07,867 --> 00:02:10,233
there's still one fugitive
who hasn't been caught yet,

30
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:11,767
but we're working on it.

31
00:02:12,733 --> 00:02:13,733
Thank you, Sir.

32
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:18,467
Also, is it true what I heard
that the pimple patch drugs case

33
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:20,267
at Calabari State University
has been solved?

34
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:22,567
Yes, you can say that.

35
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:23,800
But on our end,

36
00:02:23,933 --> 00:02:27,100
we're sure that there will be
no more

37
00:02:27,233 --> 00:02:29,167
selling of illegal substance
at that school.

38
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:31,200
Copy, Sir.
Thank you.

39
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:32,333
Thank you for your help.

40
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:34,867
Sir...

41
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:37,467
What's the update? Any leads?

42
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:40,733
None yet, Sir, but Torres and I
will check on something later.

43
00:02:40,867 --> 00:02:42,933
- Okay, let me know.
- Yes, Sir.

44
00:02:43,067 --> 00:02:44,400
I'll be right there
in the office.

45
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,600
<i> Can we start again?</i>

46
00:03:31,933 --> 00:03:32,900
<i> Please.</i>

47
00:03:33,967 --> 00:03:35,533
Okay, Sir Tonyo.

48
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:38,167
Fresh start.

49
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:50,300
Bobby...

50
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:56,900
Maybe you want to go home
and rest for a while?

51
00:03:57,067 --> 00:03:59,100
Why, Sir?
Are you sending me away?

52
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:01,933
Of course not.

53
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:07,467
I just don't want people outside
to gossip about us.

54
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:12,900
Well, just let them gossip
about us as much as they want.

55
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:14,433
Are you sure?

56
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,500
Is it okay for them
to gossip about us?

57
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:18,700
Yes, Sir.

58
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:21,467
Okay, let them gossip about us
as much as they want!

59
00:05:04,467 --> 00:05:06,067
Sir Tonyo?

60
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,800
Oh my, what happened to you?

61
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:11,000
I heard about it.
Here, I brought you some food.

62
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:12,633
Ma'am Bobby, go ahead, go home.

63
00:05:12,767 --> 00:05:15,200
I'll take care of Sir Tonyo
so you can rest.

64
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:16,133
No...

65
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,667
- Selena...
- No, Selena.

66
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,667
Sir, it's okay.

67
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:23,300
Okay, perfect timing.

68
00:05:23,433 --> 00:05:26,033
Maybe I need to report
to my grandmother.

69
00:05:26,167 --> 00:05:28,367
I'm sure, she misses me a lot.

70
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,467
Besides, I need to rest.

71
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:33,000
Selena will take care of you.

72
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:34,267
Thank you, Selena.

73
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:36,267
Sir, I'll see you tomorrow.

74
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,667
Are you sure, Bobby?

75
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,267
Yes, Sir, I'm sure.

76
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,500
Okay, thank you, Selena.

77
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:46,933
<i> Okay. Take care, Ma'am.</i>

78
00:05:47,067 --> 00:05:51,300
Sir, you'll like the food
I brought.

79
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:58,400
<i>I've got some fish here,
some soup, and lots of rice.</i>

80
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:00,100
<i> I'll put it here for now.</i>

81
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:04,567
The investigation
into the banned pimple patch

82
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:06,767
at Calabari State University
has been concluded.

83
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:09,600
The police have confirmed
that appropriate charges

84
00:06:09,767 --> 00:06:11,733
have been filed against
those involved.

85
00:06:12,033 --> 00:06:15,867
Meanwhile, Edgar Villanueva
was caught this morning

86
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:20,333
in Village Malabon, when he met
with his ex-girlfriend.

87
00:06:20,467 --> 00:06:25,733
Armando "Mando" Garrido,
alias Mandong Warak,

88
00:06:25,867 --> 00:06:28,400
who is considered the mastermind
of the prison escape,

89
00:06:28,533 --> 00:06:30,033
was killed in an encounter.

90
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:34,200
How are you, Son?

91
00:06:34,667 --> 00:06:36,833
Yeah, I'm okay, Dad.

92
00:06:36,967 --> 00:06:38,000
I know it's hard.

93
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:44,733
You know, Son, the entire
Calabari is my home.

94
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:48,267
The residents here
are my family.

95
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:53,700
I can't accept that there are
people who have no other goal

96
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:57,033
than to violate the laws
of Calabari.

97
00:06:57,867 --> 00:07:02,633
That's why it's hard to live
in a home without peace.

98
00:07:03,067 --> 00:07:04,700
Nothing I can't handle.

99
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:08,267
You should, Son, especially
now that you're vice mayor.

100
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:12,800
But, Son, I'm glad the supplier
of drugs

101
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:15,333
at Faye's school was caught.

102
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:22,367
Imagine, those suppliers
were caught at Faye's school?

103
00:07:23,567 --> 00:07:24,633
My god.

104
00:07:24,767 --> 00:07:26,833
You know, we won't stop.

105
00:07:26,967 --> 00:07:34,767
There are many more evil people
here in Calabari.

106
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:38,133
We'll take them one by one, Son.

107
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:40,367
Yes, Dad.

108
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,967
Hey, things are going crazy
here in Calabari.

109
00:07:48,133 --> 00:07:51,567
There are always big crimes
happening around.

110
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,967
The first one,
the pimple patch, remember?

111
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:56,200
Now, there are some prisoners
who have escaped.

112
00:07:56,333 --> 00:08:00,033
Bobby, how many escapees
have escaped?

113
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:01,967
Really, escapees?

114
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:04,333
Okay, spell escapees.

115
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:09,433
- Just fugitives.
- Bobby, how many have escaped?

116
00:08:09,567 --> 00:08:12,567
What, there's only one more
who hasn't been caught.

117
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:16,433
Well, what's important,
my grandchild, is you're safe.

118
00:08:16,567 --> 00:08:17,833
I'm happy now.

119
00:08:17,967 --> 00:08:20,000
I owe my life to Tonyo.

120
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,000
Tonyo?

121
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:25,300
No more "Sir"?

122
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:28,267
He's not here.

123
00:08:30,433 --> 00:08:32,933
What does that smile mean?

124
00:08:33,067 --> 00:08:34,933
Yes, Bobby, share it!

125
00:08:35,067 --> 00:08:36,300
Yes, it looks like
you're blooming.

126
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:37,433
That smile is different.

127
00:08:37,567 --> 00:08:38,767
Nothing!

128
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:39,933
You're just making intrigues.

129
00:08:40,067 --> 00:08:41,067
<i> Nothing.</i>

130
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:45,833
I'm just happy because I feel
like, from now on,

131
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:47,267
everything will be fine.

132
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:51,633
Me too, grandchild,
I'm happy because you're safe.

133
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:54,733
Grandchild...

134
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:58,833
I guess it would be happier
if you took a bath.

135
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:00,567
You smell different.

136
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:01,867
Okay!

137
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,867
Okay, Grandmother,
I'll take a bath, okay?

138
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,633
- Okay.
- You're the one who's smelly.

139
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:08,867
- Yes.
- Hey, you're too much.

140
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,567
But she stinks, doesn't she?

141
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,367
Nothing like that.

142
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,567
Hey, Roman,

143
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:17,333
Boss wants to know what your man
at the station is up to.

144
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,833
Nothing.

145
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:21,033
He can't do anything

146
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,833
because there's a tight watch
on Monty in jail,

147
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:25,000
and same with his girlfriend
too.

148
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,767
Boss won't like this,
I'm telling you.

149
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,367
Wait, wait, wait...

150
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:33,933
Are you scolding me?

151
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,733
Why are you doing nothing?

152
00:09:38,033 --> 00:09:41,667
Let me just remind you, Monty,
the guy who failed,

153
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:42,767
that's your kid.

154
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:45,467
We're both the same,
our men failed.

155
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:50,067
You know, we're not going
anywhere with this conversation.

156
00:09:51,533 --> 00:09:57,000
All we need to do is figure out
how to get Monty

157
00:09:57,133 --> 00:09:58,567
and his girlfriend out
of our way.

158
00:09:58,700 --> 00:09:59,700
It's that simple.

159
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:03,600
You know, right now,
Monty won't betray us.

160
00:10:03,767 --> 00:10:05,400
But you know, Boss.

161
00:10:05,533 --> 00:10:07,533
He doesn't like that kind
of thing.

162
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:28,067
Please!

163
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:32,200
If you can't sleep,
can you just let me sleep?

164
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,500
Sophia,

165
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:36,900
I'm sorry.

166
00:10:38,133 --> 00:10:39,767
I'm having a hard time
breathing.

167
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,767
Have you taken
your maintenance meds?

168
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:48,833
I know why you're like that.

169
00:10:48,967 --> 00:10:51,333
You'd better drink
your meds, Joaquin.

170
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:54,100
We can't afford to be
sleep-deprived tomorrow.

171
00:10:54,233 --> 00:10:56,067
You have a big day tomorrow.

172
00:10:58,233 --> 00:11:00,667
Yes, you're right.

173
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,433
There.

174
00:11:12,433 --> 00:11:14,767
Talking about the devil,
the devil's calling.

175
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,300
Boss, bad news.

176
00:11:18,433 --> 00:11:21,300
Our contact inside can't move,

177
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:26,200
and Monty and his girlfriend
are being closely monitored.

178
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:28,667
Can't you hear what I'm saying?

179
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:32,133
I don't care
what you have to do.

180
00:11:32,267 --> 00:11:34,300
I want them both gone!

181
00:11:34,433 --> 00:11:36,500
Do you understand that?

182
00:11:36,633 --> 00:11:38,433
That's clear, Boss.

183
00:11:38,567 --> 00:11:39,967
Go ahead, do it!

184
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,167
Who's that?

185
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:09,033
Get out of there!
I'll blow your head off!

186
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:11,067
Come out!

187
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,433
- Sir, no, I'm sorry!
- Manang?

188
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:16,933
Sorry! I was just doing
something in the kitchen.

189
00:13:17,067 --> 00:13:18,133
Something fell.

190
00:13:18,267 --> 00:13:19,800
I'm really sorry, Sir!

191
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,167
Glen!

192
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:25,600
- Dad.
- Do you really have to aim

193
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:26,600
at her head?

194
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:28,433
Dad, it's a protective instinct.

195
00:13:28,567 --> 00:13:29,767
I thought she was a thief.

196
00:13:32,467 --> 00:13:36,700
Manang, I'm sorry,
but it's late.

197
00:13:37,467 --> 00:13:39,667
Next time, when it's break time,
we should all rest.

198
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:41,567
Come on.

199
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,633
I'm really sorry, sorry.

200
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:46,733
I thought she was a thief.

201
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:49,500
Next time, be careful.

202
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:52,100
You might accidentally kill
someone.

203
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:53,633
I just want to be safe.

204
00:13:58,333 --> 00:13:59,433
I'll go ahead.

205
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:00,400
Okay.

206
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:27,900
Bobby!

207
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:30,900
Hey, my crush texted me.

208
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:34,167
- What did he say?
- It's the ambulance driver.

209
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:36,067
- What did he say?
- This.

210
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:39,767
- "Hi, Abdul." Jealous.
- Hey...

211
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:41,267
"How are you?"

212
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:45,467
I know that! Watch out
for the next text. Look.

213
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,200
You know, you're so negative.

214
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,167
Wait. Wait.

215
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:53,567
Here it is.
Bobby, read it.

216
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:57,833
- Right?
- Can I borrow 1k?

217
00:14:59,067 --> 00:15:01,233
Right? I told you!

218
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,900
Maybe it was just sent
by mistake.

219
00:15:04,267 --> 00:15:05,433
I'm already excited.

220
00:15:05,567 --> 00:15:08,000
Don't get so excited
about those texts!

221
00:15:08,133 --> 00:15:10,167
Text messages have no emotion.

222
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:11,567
Through the fire!

223
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:12,767
Okay.

224
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:14,700
Come on, I'm pissed off
with this.

225
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:17,300
- Let's go.
- You deserve it.

226
00:15:17,433 --> 00:15:18,567
He's so handsome.

227
00:15:24,167 --> 00:15:25,200
Hello, Jun?

228
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:26,667
It's me.

229
00:15:28,267 --> 00:15:31,333
Sorry I called you
so late at night.

230
00:15:32,567 --> 00:15:36,600
I want you to do something,
but no one must know about it.

231
00:15:36,767 --> 00:15:43,767
Follow Glen where he goes
and who he talks to.

232
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:50,933
I just want to know
if my son is human or a demon.

233
00:15:58,267 --> 00:16:02,300
<i>Hi Bobby,
are you still awake?</i>

234
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:13,467
What's with him?

235
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,767
Clingy?

236
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:18,500
<i> I'm still awake. Why?</i>

237
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:29,867
<i> Nothing, I miss you.</i>

238
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:33,967
Oh my, this guy
is something else.

239
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,733
We were just together earlier.

240
00:16:37,533 --> 00:16:38,333
Okay, fine.

241
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:40,200
<i> Me too. I miss you.</i>

242
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:45,567
<i> How's your companion there?</i>

243
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:09,933
<i> Well, she's sound asleep.</i>

244
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:16,933
<i>Can you come and visit me
tomorrow? Please.</i>

245
00:17:17,067 --> 00:17:21,000
<i> So I can get better soon.</i>

246
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:25,500
He's old already, but
he's still acting like a baby.

247
00:17:26,533 --> 00:17:27,933
Okay.

248
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:41,833
<i> Why is it just one emoji kiss?</i>

249
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:46,033
Why? How many should there be?

250
00:17:47,367 --> 00:17:48,733
Annoying...

251
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:50,800
There, that's a lot.

252
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:57,367
Oh my...

253
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,900
that's a lot.

254
00:18:00,033 --> 00:18:01,700
Competitive.

255
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:03,567
He's not giving up.

256
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:06,533
<i> Goodnight Tonyo.</i>

257
00:18:06,667 --> 00:18:09,667
<i>Goodnight, Bobby,
see you tomorrow.</i>

258
00:18:18,867 --> 00:18:21,367
Sir Tonyo, are you okay?

259
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:25,433
I'm okay, I'm okay.

260
00:18:27,533 --> 00:18:30,167
Selena, maybe you want
to go home first

261
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:32,233
so you can get some rest?

262
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:34,867
No, I'm okay here.

263
00:18:35,133 --> 00:18:37,100
Okay, good night.

264
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:49,900
Don't get so giddy
about those text messages.

265
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:52,767
Text messages have no emotion.

266
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,100
Have you been there for a while?

267
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:58,667
Girl, we'll ask, not you.

268
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,233
Are you and Tonyo together?

269
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:03,733
No comment.

270
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:05,200
No comment...

271
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:06,933
- Well, no cellphone!
- Hey, that's mine!

272
00:19:07,067 --> 00:19:09,633
- Hey! Abdul, catch!
- Hep! Abdul!

273
00:19:09,767 --> 00:19:11,900
Answer me first. Yes or no?
Final answer.

274
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:13,933
Do you love Tonyo?

275
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,367
No.

276
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,500
- Even if you die?
- Even if you die?

277
00:19:24,367 --> 00:19:26,767
I invoke my right against
self-incrimination.

278
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:29,033
Oh my! Senate hearing?

279
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,200
Oh, why?

280
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:34,167
Wait, has something happened
to you and Sir Tonyo?

281
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:38,533
Silence means yes.

282
00:19:40,967 --> 00:19:43,000
Hey, what are you doing?

283
00:19:43,133 --> 00:19:46,067
I'm sleeping, you're making
so much noise!

284
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,800
Oh my, Kapitana, sit down here.

285
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:51,067
We're having
an emergency meeting.

286
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,933
Because of Bobby,

287
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:56,667
it looks like Tonyo has been
given the Pearl of the East.

288
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,367
What? Is that true,
my grandchild?

289
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:09,733
Okay, okay.

290
00:20:09,867 --> 00:20:11,333
So you don't have
to think about it.

291
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:16,100
Nothing serious
is happening to us yet.

292
00:20:16,233 --> 00:20:17,200
What?

293
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:19,700
Nothing serious yet,
but there's something?

294
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:23,333
Bobby, there's nothing wrong
with admitting that besides,

295
00:20:23,467 --> 00:20:26,800
we're old like Kapitana.

296
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:28,467
That's right, Bobby.

297
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,567
We're not affected
by that kind of stuff,

298
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:32,500
especially that kind of talk.

299
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:35,000
Okay...

300
00:20:36,567 --> 00:20:38,333
We...

301
00:20:38,467 --> 00:20:39,767
We kissed.

302
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:43,033
Wait...

303
00:20:43,167 --> 00:20:45,000
Did you kiss once?

304
00:20:47,267 --> 00:20:48,367
How many?

305
00:20:55,167 --> 00:20:56,933
Grandchild, I know you.

306
00:20:57,067 --> 00:20:58,967
Is there something
you're not telling me?

307
00:20:59,100 --> 00:21:01,000
Did you just kiss?

308
00:21:01,133 --> 00:21:08,733
I almost gave up
the Pearl of the East.

309
00:21:13,467 --> 00:21:14,800
- Ouch!
- Ouch!

310
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:18,000
Kapitana, what you're doing
is violence against women!

311
00:21:18,133 --> 00:21:18,700
True!

312
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:20,367
We're just happy for Bobby,

313
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:21,600
- aren't we?
- Yes!

314
00:21:21,733 --> 00:21:23,700
- She got 2.
- We're so happy.

315
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:24,800
Grandmother...

316
00:21:26,333 --> 00:21:30,533
I'm sorry because I don't know
how to tell you.

317
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:34,967
But we're not yet together.

318
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:37,367
- You're not together yet?
- What's that?

319
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:39,200
No label!

320
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:43,933
Well, grandchild,
I like Sir Tonyo for you,

321
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:46,367
but isn't it better if...

322
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:51,033
You'll work hard for something,
especially in love?

323
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:57,667
We, too, Bobby, we like
Sir Tonyo, but without a label?

324
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,733
That seems like a red flag.

325
00:21:59,867 --> 00:22:02,500
Actually, it's a very red flag.

326
00:22:02,633 --> 00:22:04,267
Wait, Bobby.

327
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:06,800
How long has Tonyo
been courting you for that long?

328
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:12,967
Well, he's not really courting.

329
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:15,200
Not courting you?

330
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:20,900
Bobby, sometimes,
these gays have a point.

331
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:24,700
If you get something quickly,

332
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:27,500
most likely they are going
to disappear just as quickly.

333
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:32,667
We like Sir Tonyo
for but we should go through

334
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:38,233
the proper process to be sure,
so that you don't get hurt.

335
00:22:40,533 --> 00:22:41,767
I'm a plus one there.

336
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,900
Do you know of a place
to buy flowers near here?

337
00:23:04,033 --> 00:23:06,133
Sir Tonyo is asking me
to buy flowers.

338
00:23:06,267 --> 00:23:07,767
He said he's going
to surprise a woman.

339
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:08,800
You don't need to surprise me.

340
00:23:08,933 --> 00:23:10,700
You're even asking Vince
to do something.

341
00:23:10,833 --> 00:23:11,900
What do you mean?

342
00:23:12,033 --> 00:23:13,167
Excuse me, I have to take this.

343
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,700
Should you still stand up?
Who are you talking to?

344
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:16,933
Can I talk to him?

345
00:23:17,067 --> 00:23:17,800
Hi, Bobby!

346
00:23:17,933 --> 00:23:19,300
I have something written.

347
00:23:19,433 --> 00:23:20,400
I would like you to hear it.

348
00:23:20,533 --> 00:23:23,433
A beautiful day, beautiful lady.

349
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:26,133
We have a boss,
you are the one he chose.

350
00:23:26,267 --> 00:23:29,033
You are the reason
for the smile on his lips.

351
00:23:29,167 --> 00:23:31,067
He loves someone,
and her name is...

352
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,033
Bobby!
